This paper involves deep learning techniques for image recognition and classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for identifying conceptual shifts, which could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a co-creative drawing system, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
